<center><font size=7><b>Feud</b></font></center>
<center>Number of entries found: 3</center><p>
<center>
<table width=600>
<TR><TD bgcolor="blue" background=""><font color="white"><b><i>Tips</i></b></font></td></tr>
<TR><TD>Always look for herbs which make up missile spells like Fireball, Lightning
and Sprites as these are more effective.<br>

&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Once you've armed yourself with a spell, never leave the book open at the
correspon- dance page as the spell will disappear if you do.<br>

&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Beware when entering the herb garden (bottom left on the map) as there is a
guardian which chases you and drains your energy.<br>

&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;To kill Leanoric quickly, simply arm yourself with three missile spells and
wait by your cauldron.&nbsp; Leanoric will appear after a while, totally
vulnerable to your spells.<br>

&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;If you find that Leanoric has a herb before you, just move into a
neighbouring screen and wait for a minute or two.  Then re-enter the screen
and the herb will be back again.!<br>

&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Here are the spells you need:<br>

&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Teleport - this spell will teleport from anywhere you like back to your cauldron<br>

&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Protect - this one will make you invulnerable for a short while<br>

&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Sprites - this is a missile spell<br>

&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Zombie - this will create a slow moving zomble that'll follow you around.
If Leanoric is on the screen the zombie will appear on top of him, draining
his energy<br>

&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Swift - this allows you to move at twice the speed for a short time<br>

&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Freeze - if Leanoric is on the screen, this will stop him from moving<br>

&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Doppleganger - will produce a replica of you which will divert Leanoric's
attention while you do other things<br>

&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Lightning - a missile spell<br>

&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Invisible - guess what this does?<br>

&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Reverse - will make Leanoric move in the opposite direction to the one he wants to<br>

&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Heal - self explanatory<br>

&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Fireball - a missile spell
 <i>(David McCandless in Your Sinclair issue 18)</i> 
<br>
</td></tr>
<TR><TD bgcolor="blue" background=""><font color="white"><b><i>Multiface pokes</i></b></font></td></tr>
<TR><TD><table border="0">
<tr>
<td WIDTH="200" ALIGN="LEFT"><B><U>DESCRIPTION</B></U></TD>
<td WIDTH="200" ALIGN="LEFT"><B><U>POKE(s)</B></U></TD>
</TR>
<tr><td>Infinite Energy</td><td>51425,0:51447,0</td></tr>
</table>
<BR><BR><B>If anyone finds&nbsp;out if this works, <a href="mailto:tipshop@ysrnry.co.uk">let me know</A></B><br>

&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <i>(Gerard Sweeney in Hack Attack III)</i> 
<br>
</td></tr>
<TR><TD bgcolor="blue" background=""><font color="white"><b><i>Type-in hacks</i></b></font></td></tr>
<TR><TD>For infinite energy, Merge the loader and add this to line 4 before the
RANDOMIZE USR;<br>

&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;LET a=51425: POKE a,0: POKE a+22,0: POKE a+68.201:
 <i>(YS Smash Tips)</i> 
<br>
</td></tr>
</table></center><P>
